---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Avatar  from "../../images/oip.jpg";

---

<Layout title='Blog'>
  <h1>About Me</h1>
  <hr class="my-8">
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 text-center items-center">
    <span class="items-center text-center">
      <div class="w-48 h-48 rounded-full overflow-hidden mx-auto">
        <Image src={Avatar} alt='profile picture' format='webp'/>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl">Sompon Onlume</h1>
    </span>
    <span>
      <p class="mt-4 text-xl">Hello! I'm Best, currently study at Kasetsart University in the Faculty of Computer Engineering. 
        I've already learn about web development, and still practice my skills in full-stack projects.</p>
      <h2>My Journey So Far</h2>
      <p>My journey into the realm of coding and development began during my time at university. With a passion for learning to code and found the web development to be the most interesting,
         I've doing project about full-stack web projects, gaining hands-on experience in both front-end and back-end development.</p>
      <h2>Embracing the Learning Curve</h2>
      <p>As a student, I'm currently learning about machine learning. I'm excited to explore the this area I think it gonna be useful in the future to learning this skills</p>
    </span>
</Layout>